1
00:00:39,070 --> 00:00:40,540
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

2
00:00:40,540 --> 00:00:41,970
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

3
00:00:44,810 --> 00:00:46,750
(Episode 10)

4
00:01:08,230 --> 00:01:11,040
Mr. Ha is a bit superstitious, isn't he?

5
00:01:11,870 --> 00:01:14,470
I've heard a lot of celebrities
are into that.

6
00:01:14,770 --> 00:01:17,710
Usually, it's the agency heads
who seek those things out.

7
00:01:18,380 --> 00:01:21,180
But at my company,
they were all raised Christian,

8
00:01:21,650 --> 00:01:22,750
so they can't stand it.

9
00:01:23,020 --> 00:01:24,920
Are you thinking of seeing someone?

10
00:01:25,020 --> 00:01:27,590
Just from time to time.

11
00:01:28,350 --> 00:01:30,390
I wish my mom had gone to see one.

12
00:01:30,690 --> 00:01:35,190
I sometimes think it would've been
better than therapy.

13
00:01:36,760 --> 00:01:39,400
I wish there were a pill that would
let me sleep for a few years.

14
00:01:44,240 --> 00:01:46,710
You don't have a care in the world,
do you?

15
00:01:49,740 --> 00:01:52,680
- You do?
- I've been through my fair share...

16
00:01:53,050 --> 00:01:54,110
when I was developing my game.

17
00:01:54,810 --> 00:01:56,950
There was no guarantee of success.

18
00:01:57,780 --> 00:02:00,620
I was getting older, and I only had a GED.

19
00:02:01,520 --> 00:02:03,460
Who was your celebrity crush?

20
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:05,760
I didn't have one.

21
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:08,290
What about now?

22
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:12,100
I never said I did.

23
00:02:12,930 --> 00:02:16,470
You said you "didn't," past tense.
Doesn't that mean you have one now?

24
00:02:17,700 --> 00:02:18,770
You're right. I should be honest.

25
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:21,240
Of course you should.

26
00:02:23,080 --> 00:02:24,080
It's you, Momo.

27
00:02:26,180 --> 00:02:27,210
Oh, my.

28
00:02:27,750 --> 00:02:28,750
Really?

29
00:02:29,480 --> 00:02:30,520
Yes.

30
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:31,850
From what role?

31
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:34,250
I didn't fall for one of your characters.

32
00:02:35,920 --> 00:02:37,420
I guess you could say I fell for you.

33
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:41,490
But you don't even really know me.

34
00:02:42,090 --> 00:02:43,530
If it weren't for Ju Shin,

35
00:02:43,530 --> 00:02:46,200
you wouldn't have even known I existed,
would you?

36
00:02:46,630 --> 00:02:47,670
That may be true.

37
00:02:53,340 --> 00:02:56,740
I heard games were everything
to you from Mr. Ha.

38
00:02:56,810 --> 00:02:58,040
That's not wrong.

39
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:01,250
I bet my life on them.

40
00:03:01,850 --> 00:03:04,550
Are you going to keep
dedicating your life to work?

41
00:03:04,820 --> 00:03:06,690
It's not like I'm doing it all
by myself anymore,

42
00:03:07,720 --> 00:03:10,390
and I'm starting to think
I want to live like other people.

43
00:03:11,220 --> 00:03:13,690
But anyway, my brother has to
get married first.

44
00:03:14,630 --> 00:03:16,400
That's going to be tough for Mr. Ha.

45
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:18,260
His standards are sky-high.

46
00:03:20,900 --> 00:03:22,130
I'm right here.

47
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:24,270
Look no further.

48
00:03:25,370 --> 00:03:26,470
What is it?

49
00:03:28,570 --> 00:03:30,680
The chef wanted to know
how you enjoyed your meal.

50
00:03:30,910 --> 00:03:33,280
The portions were a bit large,
but it was excellent.

51
00:03:33,810 --> 00:03:35,750
- Same here.
- I'll pass that along.

52
00:03:40,550 --> 00:03:41,890
You have a bigger appetite
than I expected.

53
00:03:43,220 --> 00:03:44,660
I'm at the right age for it.

54
00:03:47,230 --> 00:03:51,700
My late mother used to love seeing
people heartily enjoy their food.

55
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,940
That's such a sweet memory.

56
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:57,470
I wonder if our dinner tonight...

57
00:03:59,070 --> 00:04:00,410
will become a fond memory too.

58
00:04:03,480 --> 00:04:04,910
Do you have surgery tomorrow?

59
00:04:05,410 --> 00:04:06,480
Pretty much every day.

60
00:04:07,880 --> 00:04:09,320
Whatever you do,
don't take up horseback riding.

61
00:04:10,450 --> 00:04:11,480
So many people get injured.

62
00:04:12,020 --> 00:04:13,590
Seungil Shipping's youngest daughter...

63
00:04:13,590 --> 00:04:16,390
She had a bad fall two years ago,
and I struggled to treat her concussion,

64
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:17,790
but she went riding again...

65
00:04:18,990 --> 00:04:21,330
They say riding horses is
more addictive than meth.

66
00:04:21,330 --> 00:04:22,500
Is it really that bad?

67
00:04:23,830 --> 00:04:27,030
- Is that a real saying?
- Yes, it is.

68
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:28,800
Can't say the same for
cows or sheep, though.

69
00:04:37,780 --> 00:04:39,380
You're surprisingly quirky and fun.

70
00:04:46,190 --> 00:04:47,620
Who's texting you this late?

71
00:04:47,620 --> 00:04:48,690
It's for my taxi.

72
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:51,320
- I will drive you.
- No, that's okay.

73
00:04:52,190 --> 00:04:53,230
I'm not sure how to feel about that.

74
00:04:55,700 --> 00:04:56,730
Are you wary of me?

75
00:04:57,500 --> 00:04:58,500
Yes.

76
00:04:59,930 --> 00:05:02,370
A woman has to be careful these days.

77
00:05:02,870 --> 00:05:04,440
Isn't it rude to be that honest?

78
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:10,610
I don't want to impose.

79
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:13,450
How is it an imposition?
My driver's waiting.

80
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:30,600
Please don't get out.

81
00:05:34,730 --> 00:05:35,740
Thank you.

82
00:05:36,570 --> 00:05:37,570
Alright.

83
00:05:50,220 --> 00:05:51,220
What is it?

84
00:06:00,590 --> 00:06:01,590
What's wrong?

85
00:06:03,030 --> 00:06:04,230
I feel dizzy.

86
00:06:04,930 --> 00:06:05,970
Dizzy how?

87
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:08,500
Open your eyes.

88
00:06:09,270 --> 00:06:10,840
I can't.

89
00:06:11,140 --> 00:06:12,140
Open them.

90
00:06:13,070 --> 00:06:14,110
What's the passcode?

91
00:06:14,870 --> 00:06:16,310
It's 1103.

92
00:06:51,710 --> 00:06:53,050
I've got you.

93
00:06:53,580 --> 00:06:54,850
It'll pass soon.

94
00:06:56,080 --> 00:07:00,090
Okay, first, I'm going to turn your head
to the left, 45 degrees.

95
00:07:07,690 --> 00:07:08,990
I'm going to count to 35.

96
00:07:09,500 --> 00:07:12,400
One, two, three,

97
00:07:13,230 --> 00:07:14,230
four...

98
00:07:21,170 --> 00:07:22,370
You'll feel better soon.

99
00:07:23,240 --> 00:07:26,150
One, two, three...

100
00:07:29,350 --> 00:07:30,820
Ever think about getting on
an operating table?

101
00:07:32,350 --> 00:07:35,750
Lie down just once,
and I can change your life.

102
00:07:39,260 --> 00:07:40,260
Go on in.

103
00:07:42,060 --> 00:07:44,360
I'm sorry. It was an important call.

104
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:45,530
Of course.

105
00:08:14,260 --> 00:08:15,630
Have you ever been to this house?

106
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:17,400
No.

107
00:08:18,030 --> 00:08:19,430
My father never invited you over?

108
00:08:19,870 --> 00:08:23,000
- No.
- Are you feeling better?

109
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:24,800
Yes.

110
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:28,910
I've barely been here
since my father passed.

111
00:08:29,510 --> 00:08:30,510
I just don't find myself stopping by.

112
00:08:31,210 --> 00:08:34,410
They say a house needs people living in it
to keep it from falling apart.

113
00:08:36,550 --> 00:08:37,580
That rock...

114
00:08:38,450 --> 00:08:39,950
is really cool and refreshing to sit on.

115
00:08:40,450 --> 00:08:42,860
When I got sleepy from studying,
I'd come out here to wake myself up.

116
00:08:45,290 --> 00:08:46,630
You don't like small dogs?

117
00:08:49,030 --> 00:08:51,760
Maybe it's because I was small and skinny.

118
00:08:51,900 --> 00:08:53,270
I'm drawn to big dogs.

119
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:55,970
But he isn't a big dog.

120
00:08:56,500 --> 00:09:00,070
How am I supposed to raise a Retriever
in Yong Joong's apartment?

121
00:09:08,780 --> 00:09:10,420
You can raise ten Retrievers...

122
00:09:10,980 --> 00:09:11,980
in this house.

123
00:09:12,550 --> 00:09:15,590
Border Collies, Jindo dogs,
Chow Chows, Tibetan Mastiffs...

124
00:09:16,860 --> 00:09:19,830
You can have all the dogs you want,

125
00:09:20,830 --> 00:09:22,430
and we can live here, together.

126
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:27,500
It's cliché, but I'm proposing...

127
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:32,840
over two glasses of cold water.

128
00:09:36,010 --> 00:09:37,280
I'm not asking for much.

129
00:09:39,210 --> 00:09:41,510
Just have my children and raise them well.

130
00:09:43,620 --> 00:09:44,950
I think we're on the same wavelength...

131
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:47,790
when we talk or have any thoughts.

132
00:09:49,390 --> 00:09:51,190
I can have a decent conversation...

133
00:09:52,220 --> 00:09:54,260
- with just about anyone...
- I can't.

134
00:09:55,290 --> 00:09:56,360
I'm selective.

135
00:09:59,630 --> 00:10:01,430
Stop overthinking and complicating things.

136
00:10:01,430 --> 00:10:03,500
It's not about conditions...

137
00:10:04,470 --> 00:10:05,970
I'm not qualified,

138
00:10:07,070 --> 00:10:08,240
and we're not a match.

139
00:10:08,840 --> 00:10:09,840
What isn't?

140
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:23,190
Look, we're both on our own now.
No parents, no siblings.

141
00:10:24,460 --> 00:10:25,560
So what doesn't match?

142
00:10:25,960 --> 00:10:27,730
I've never even considered it.

143
00:10:28,330 --> 00:10:29,660
And it's completely out of the question.

144
00:10:29,660 --> 00:10:31,430
Nothing's out of the question.

145
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:34,330
Everything people do is
more or less the same.

146
00:10:34,870 --> 00:10:35,870
Marriage.

147
00:10:36,340 --> 00:10:37,870
They call it one of
life's most important events,

148
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:40,210
but it's just a man and a woman
living together.

149
00:10:40,210 --> 00:10:41,510
What's so special about that?

150
00:10:42,540 --> 00:10:43,840
Isn't it meaningful...

151
00:10:44,480 --> 00:10:47,210
to stay together with hearts unchanged
and not to get a divorce?

152
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:50,280
I know what you mean.

153
00:10:50,920 --> 00:10:52,150
You're not wrong,

154
00:10:53,820 --> 00:10:55,150
but you never know until you try.

155
00:10:58,160 --> 00:10:59,460
So you're rejecting me
without a second thought?

156
00:11:00,190 --> 00:11:01,730
I'm taking that to mean
you find me completely undesirable.

157
00:11:02,330 --> 00:11:03,400
It's the opposite.

158
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:05,330
You know best that,

159
00:11:05,600 --> 00:11:07,730
as for qualifications,
I'm the worst possible choice.

160
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:09,670
I said let's not worry
about qualifications.

161
00:11:10,970 --> 00:11:12,870
I don't know my roots.

162
00:11:21,450 --> 00:11:22,720
The first humans...

163
00:11:23,750 --> 00:11:26,420
Think about the first life-form.
Did it have roots?

164
00:11:27,690 --> 00:11:29,820
The sky was their father
and the earth was their mother, right?

165
00:11:31,220 --> 00:11:32,590
Like the digital zero and one,

166
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:35,760
life began from the combination
of yin and yang.

167
00:11:37,960 --> 00:11:39,570
Are these so-called qualifications
that people came up with...

168
00:11:40,630 --> 00:11:42,600
really that important?

169
00:11:45,540 --> 00:11:47,140
That's all they are. Just things.

170
00:11:47,840 --> 00:11:50,480
- You have a point, but...
- If I have a point, then don't argue.

171
00:11:54,250 --> 00:11:55,410
You don't see me as a man?

172
00:11:57,380 --> 00:11:58,480
To be honest...

173
00:11:58,980 --> 00:12:00,550
Then start now.

174
00:12:01,090 --> 00:12:02,220
You could at least try.

175
00:12:06,430 --> 00:12:07,890
As a man, I'm flawless.

176
00:12:15,630 --> 00:12:17,040
A loveless marriage?

177
00:12:17,470 --> 00:12:18,770
Do you even know what love is?

178
00:12:19,810 --> 00:12:21,840
Define it. What is it?

179
00:12:27,580 --> 00:12:30,380
- Haven't you ever told Momo you love her?
- Leave Momo out of this.

180
00:12:31,050 --> 00:12:32,050
This is about us.

181
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:34,590
I'm interested in you, Geum Ba Ra.

182
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:36,020
Since when?

183
00:12:37,160 --> 00:12:39,660
This interest of yours could just fade.

184
00:12:39,790 --> 00:12:40,790
Even if it does,

185
00:12:42,900 --> 00:12:45,400
- let's do it.
- What are you really thinking?

186
00:12:46,060 --> 00:12:48,130
Is it like, "I'm not hungry,
but the table's set."

187
00:12:48,130 --> 00:12:50,640
"Even if it's not appealing,
let's just go through with it?"

188
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:52,240
- Is that what this is?
- No.

189
00:12:52,910 --> 00:12:54,110
Stop questioning me.

190
00:12:58,540 --> 00:12:59,580
I hate complications.

191
00:13:00,950 --> 00:13:02,410
And I especially hate
having to explain myself.

192
00:13:03,780 --> 00:13:06,320
If you were my patient,
I'd patiently explain everything to you.

193
00:13:08,090 --> 00:13:09,760
I really can't.

194
00:13:09,760 --> 00:13:10,920
Because of your background?

195
00:13:12,460 --> 00:13:13,630
Or are you saying the problem is me?

196
00:13:13,630 --> 00:13:14,730
It's both.

197
00:13:15,890 --> 00:13:17,000
I'm sorry.

198
00:13:17,630 --> 00:13:19,000
But I do appreciate...

199
00:13:21,270 --> 00:13:22,530
you thinking so highly of me.

200
00:13:26,070 --> 00:13:27,210
I should get going.

201
00:13:32,180 --> 00:13:33,450
Is it because of Momo?

202
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:39,120
Is that what's holding you back?

203
00:13:40,450 --> 00:13:41,750
That's part of the reason, yes.

204
00:13:42,290 --> 00:13:44,690
We're like sisters.
It just wouldn't be right.

205
00:13:48,730 --> 00:13:49,860
What's that supposed to mean?

206
00:13:58,540 --> 00:14:00,770
Don't take a cab with the dog.
They'll give you a hard time.

207
00:14:01,710 --> 00:14:02,880
Nurse Park should be around.

208
00:14:53,560 --> 00:14:54,560
And so?

209
00:14:55,060 --> 00:14:57,600
Ankle monitors are for violent criminals,
right?

210
00:14:58,800 --> 00:15:01,070
I was so scared, and I was shaking.

211
00:15:01,570 --> 00:15:03,940
- Do you have his number?
- What are you planning to do?

212
00:15:05,240 --> 00:15:07,540
What if he holds a grudge against me?

213
00:15:07,910 --> 00:15:10,410
We'll have to figure something out
without confronting him.

214
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:11,780
If he shows up again,

215
00:15:11,780 --> 00:15:14,150
tell security first,
then call me right away.

216
00:15:17,920 --> 00:15:18,920
Got it?

217
00:15:22,620 --> 00:15:24,690
I've become such a coward lately.

218
00:15:25,720 --> 00:15:27,060
I have no confidence in anything,

219
00:15:27,730 --> 00:15:29,630
and I keep having memory lapses.

220
00:15:30,530 --> 00:15:31,700
Lapses? How so?

221
00:15:32,160 --> 00:15:35,930
I can't remember bits and pieces
of my interactions with people.

222
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:41,240
So if I ever forget something,
please try to understand.

223
00:15:42,140 --> 00:15:43,980
My doctor said that could happen.

224
00:15:45,340 --> 00:15:46,680
Your psychiatrist?

225
00:15:47,850 --> 00:15:50,250
I was just grasping at straws.

226
00:15:50,850 --> 00:15:53,420
I can't even trust myself anymore.

227
00:16:00,530 --> 00:16:03,100
I'm not very emotionally stable,

228
00:16:03,630 --> 00:16:06,030
and there's no way
I can get married in this state.

229
00:16:06,830 --> 00:16:07,830
So...

230
00:16:10,270 --> 00:16:11,370
Can't you understand?

231
00:16:12,270 --> 00:16:14,340
Putting myself in your shoes, I get it.

232
00:16:16,880 --> 00:16:17,880
Please eat.

233
00:16:18,380 --> 00:16:20,480
I barely notice my hunger these days.

234
00:16:20,650 --> 00:16:21,810
Would you like some wine?

235
00:16:22,710 --> 00:16:23,750
No, that's okay.

236
00:16:24,320 --> 00:16:27,090
The atmosphere here is so comfortable,
I don't need a drink.

237
00:16:28,050 --> 00:16:29,350
I guess I feel at ease...

238
00:16:29,920 --> 00:16:31,560
because I'm with you.

239
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:37,400
Go ahead.

240
00:16:38,260 --> 00:16:41,000
To be honest,
hard liquor is more my style than wine.

241
00:16:41,770 --> 00:16:42,800
Whiskey, then.

242
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:45,970
My treat. You're so busy,
but you still made time for me.

243
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:48,510
No, I'm not really looking
to get drunk tonight.

244
00:16:50,510 --> 00:16:51,610
I'm just enjoying our conversation.

245
00:17:02,050 --> 00:17:04,020
Since you two are friends,

246
00:17:04,720 --> 00:17:08,460
I won't tell you how lonely and upset
Ju Shin made me feel.

247
00:17:08,630 --> 00:17:10,760
His upbringing probably
had something to do with it.

248
00:17:12,300 --> 00:17:14,530
To live up to
the late Director's expectations,

249
00:17:15,030 --> 00:17:16,900
Ju Shin worked really hard.

250
00:17:18,170 --> 00:17:19,770
I, at least, got to mess around
back in the day.

251
00:17:22,110 --> 00:17:23,480
Just try to remember the good times.

252
00:17:24,240 --> 00:17:25,240
Okay.

253
00:17:25,710 --> 00:17:28,110
The way you're explaining
everything so calmly...

254
00:17:28,410 --> 00:17:30,950
makes me feel a little less hurt.

255
00:17:33,550 --> 00:17:35,390
It must be hard for you to get away.

256
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:38,920
I'll make time.

257
00:17:40,560 --> 00:17:43,430
You can be more casual with me,
like you are with Ba Ra.

258
00:17:45,260 --> 00:17:46,260
Got it.

259
00:17:47,300 --> 00:17:49,570
You're not this formal with her.

260
00:18:10,990 --> 00:18:13,360
He's way more down-to-earth
than Director Shin.

261
00:18:14,490 --> 00:18:16,390
And I am so ready.

262
00:18:35,510 --> 00:18:38,350
(Director Shin)

263
00:18:45,590 --> 00:18:47,690
What? Is your phone face down?

264
00:18:49,630 --> 00:18:51,930
- Yes.
- You made it home okay.

265
00:18:53,330 --> 00:18:54,330
Yes.

266
00:18:55,370 --> 00:18:56,400
Let me see you.

267
00:18:58,840 --> 00:18:59,970
This is awkward.

268
00:19:01,510 --> 00:19:03,540
What's there to be awkward about?
I've already seen your place.

269
00:19:04,480 --> 00:19:05,580
Did you wash your face already?

270
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:07,880
No.

271
00:19:09,080 --> 00:19:10,080
Then what?

272
00:19:12,050 --> 00:19:14,250
I'm not a big fan of video calls.

273
00:19:15,490 --> 00:19:17,060
It's awkward for me, too,

274
00:19:17,760 --> 00:19:18,890
but the moon is just so bright.

275
00:19:19,560 --> 00:19:20,560
It's a full moon.

276
00:19:22,590 --> 00:19:23,930
Go take a look outside.

277
00:19:24,760 --> 00:19:25,760
Okay.

278
00:19:26,260 --> 00:19:27,270
You're hanging up?

279
00:19:28,570 --> 00:19:29,570
Yes.

280
00:19:31,570 --> 00:19:32,570
But I don't want you to.

281
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:34,410
I want to keep talking.

282
00:19:36,610 --> 00:19:38,340
The driver didn't give you
a hard time, did he?

283
00:19:39,410 --> 00:19:41,650
No, he was very nice.

284
00:19:43,550 --> 00:19:45,320
And here I thought
my proposal was considerate.

285
00:19:46,720 --> 00:19:48,050
Only to get shot down spectacularly.

286
00:19:50,490 --> 00:19:52,220
I'm not a big fan of
the whole marriage process either.

287
00:19:53,120 --> 00:19:55,060
It's all for show anyway.

288
00:19:56,160 --> 00:19:58,000
Let's just see each other once in a while,

289
00:19:59,100 --> 00:20:00,370
grab a meal, talk,

290
00:20:01,830 --> 00:20:03,300
and raise a baby together like that.

291
00:20:07,210 --> 00:20:08,240
You don't like that idea either?

292
00:20:08,540 --> 00:20:10,010
That doesn't feel right.

293
00:20:11,380 --> 00:20:12,410
You say no to everything.

294
00:20:14,110 --> 00:20:15,580
Don't you want to be a mother?

295
00:20:18,550 --> 00:20:21,190
To be honest, I don't think
I'd be a very good husband either.

296
00:20:21,490 --> 00:20:23,760
Love is important to me, too.

297
00:20:25,820 --> 00:20:27,230
Are you just going to wait around
forever for love?

298
00:20:33,930 --> 00:20:36,970
I feel like we're a terrible match
and a great match at the same time.

299
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:39,400
At least, I do.

300
00:20:39,800 --> 00:20:41,510
You were raised like a prince,

301
00:20:42,210 --> 00:20:44,140
and emotionally, you're a bit...

302
00:20:44,440 --> 00:20:45,440
A bit what?

303
00:20:45,880 --> 00:20:48,280
Cold? Or maybe detached?

304
00:20:49,050 --> 00:20:50,580
I'm sure it's your job, though.

305
00:20:51,950 --> 00:20:53,020
Someone's told me that before.

306
00:20:54,150 --> 00:20:55,690
That I can be pretty inconsiderate.

307
00:20:56,290 --> 00:20:57,390
And I admit it.

308
00:20:58,320 --> 00:20:59,960
You just swapped "inconsiderate"
for "emotionally detached."

309
00:21:01,090 --> 00:21:02,690
What can I do? That's just how I'm wired.

310
00:21:03,260 --> 00:21:05,830
As long as you're not bothering anyone,
it's fine.

311
00:21:06,360 --> 00:21:07,630
Do you really think so?

312
00:21:08,330 --> 00:21:10,840
- Yes.
- Then don't just think it.

313
00:21:11,100 --> 00:21:12,100
Warm up to me.

314
00:21:13,470 --> 00:21:14,840
I was looking at the moon,

315
00:21:14,840 --> 00:21:16,680
and I thought about how you rejected me.

316
00:21:18,040 --> 00:21:20,350
I wondered, "Why was I rejected?"
I just kept thinking...

317
00:21:21,310 --> 00:21:23,850
I got it wrong.
I really thought you'd say yes.

318
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:27,390
You're not the type...

319
00:21:28,790 --> 00:21:30,060
to play hard to get.

320
00:21:31,490 --> 00:21:34,990
I'd cleared my schedule
for a week to marry Momo,

321
00:21:36,490 --> 00:21:37,900
so how about we take a
walking-and-reading tour?

322
00:21:40,800 --> 00:21:41,800
A trip?

323
00:21:42,070 --> 00:21:44,200
Yes. Provence is a great place to walk.

324
00:21:44,800 --> 00:21:46,440
The scenery is a work of art
everywhere you go.

325
00:21:49,210 --> 00:21:50,540
And you're on leave from work.

326
00:21:50,610 --> 00:21:51,780
I'll be the one to compromise again.

327
00:21:53,240 --> 00:21:54,580
We don't have to have kids.

328
00:21:54,710 --> 00:21:55,780
We can just be friends
who understand each other.

329
00:21:55,850 --> 00:21:58,450
I can't possibly see you as a friend,
Director Shin.

330
00:22:00,450 --> 00:22:01,820
You don't have to force it.

331
00:22:02,950 --> 00:22:05,090
- As just an acquaintance then.
- Not even as an acquaintance.

332
00:22:05,990 --> 00:22:06,990
Then what am I supposed to do?

333
00:22:09,190 --> 00:22:11,760
- You should talk to Momo again...
- Don't mention Momo.

334
00:22:12,160 --> 00:22:14,900
I've already put her out of my mind.
I've erased her.

335
00:22:16,070 --> 00:22:18,470
I don't have the luxury or the reason
to dwell on bad memories.

336
00:22:18,540 --> 00:22:20,070
Is it really that easy for you?

337
00:22:24,280 --> 00:22:27,310
But don't you have more loving memories
than bad ones?

338
00:22:28,250 --> 00:22:29,380
She lost my baby.

339
00:22:31,450 --> 00:22:33,520
- She didn't on purpose...
- Let's not talk about that.

340
00:22:35,250 --> 00:22:37,520
Go inside before the mosquitoes get you.

341
00:22:37,520 --> 00:22:38,620
Are you worried about me?

342
00:22:42,190 --> 00:22:43,190
Alright.

343
00:22:44,260 --> 00:22:45,800
Make sure you look at the moon.

344
00:22:46,660 --> 00:22:48,430
It's been years
since I've really looked at the moon.

345
00:22:50,900 --> 00:22:52,270
Anyway,
the universe is a mysterious place.

346
00:22:53,070 --> 00:22:54,070
Yes.

347
00:22:54,910 --> 00:22:56,570
Do your premonitions usually come true?

348
00:23:00,350 --> 00:23:01,810
The one I just had...

349
00:23:04,820 --> 00:23:06,280
showed me that in the end,
you'll be by my side.

350
00:23:07,320 --> 00:23:08,320
Geum Ba Ra.

351
00:23:12,990 --> 00:23:14,860
(Geum Ba Ra)

352
00:23:45,560 --> 00:23:48,390
Do you really think he came
just for his daughter's picture?

353
00:23:48,830 --> 00:23:50,930
If he's her father, it's understandable.

354
00:23:51,760 --> 00:23:52,760
Yong Joong.

355
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:55,670
You're nine years older than me.

356
00:23:56,870 --> 00:23:57,970
Just for today.

357
00:23:59,340 --> 00:24:01,210
It's a hard habit to break.

358
00:24:03,240 --> 00:24:06,440
Anyway, if he comes back,
don't roll down your window.

359
00:24:12,020 --> 00:24:14,020
Have you ever met Kim Jin Ju?

360
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:01,200
Who is it?

361
00:25:02,130 --> 00:25:03,130
I'm an employee.

362
00:25:03,700 --> 00:25:06,500
I'm here to drop off Mr. Ha's outfit
for tomorrow.

363
00:25:07,240 --> 00:25:09,440
Right. I'm heading into the room,

364
00:25:10,010 --> 00:25:11,010
so you can come out.

365
00:25:13,480 --> 00:25:14,480
Okay.

366
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:40,970
You don't remember me, do you?

367
00:25:42,840 --> 00:25:46,510
You gave me a ride last summer
on a rainy day.

368
00:25:47,010 --> 00:25:48,850
You even gave me 100 dollars
for the taxi too.

369
00:25:51,620 --> 00:25:52,920
In front of my brother's company?

370
00:25:53,820 --> 00:25:55,850
- Yes.
- So you got the job?

371
00:25:56,550 --> 00:25:57,690
Yes, thanks to you.

372
00:25:57,960 --> 00:25:59,420
I didn't really do anything.

373
00:25:59,790 --> 00:26:02,790
- Good for you.
- I'll just leave the taxi fare here.

374
00:26:03,260 --> 00:26:04,960
I was so grateful that day.

375
00:26:05,600 --> 00:26:07,600
Treat me to a meal instead.

376
00:26:10,070 --> 00:26:12,070
I'll just leave the taxi fare here.

377
00:26:12,470 --> 00:26:14,210
I was so grateful that day.

378
00:26:15,140 --> 00:26:16,140
Don't worry about it.

379
00:26:24,420 --> 00:26:25,420
I'll be going now.

380
00:26:25,850 --> 00:26:26,850
Okay.

381
00:26:41,170 --> 00:26:43,000
He had a killer body.

382
00:26:43,500 --> 00:26:45,700
I knew her because
she worked for my brother.

383
00:26:47,070 --> 00:26:48,640
But she looked like
a completely different person...

384
00:26:49,310 --> 00:26:50,740
in that photo in the recent article.

385
00:26:52,480 --> 00:26:54,610
She's gotten a lot prettier
working with me.

386
00:26:56,310 --> 00:26:59,520
First, my mom passes away,
and now my stylist...

387
00:27:00,820 --> 00:27:02,920
When it rains, it pours.

388
00:27:04,090 --> 00:27:06,020
I really need to hold it together.

389
00:27:06,290 --> 00:27:09,360
But having Ba Ra around
must be a big help, right?

390
00:27:11,030 --> 00:27:12,730
She's lonely to the bone.

391
00:27:13,200 --> 00:27:16,330
So being around her can really
bring you down sometimes.

392
00:27:17,740 --> 00:27:18,740
Really?

393
00:27:19,200 --> 00:27:22,270
Yes.
Your upbringing really makes a difference.

394
00:27:25,440 --> 00:27:26,740
Can't you tell?

395
00:27:27,810 --> 00:27:28,810
Not really...

396
00:27:31,020 --> 00:27:32,120
Enjoy your meal.

397
00:27:32,380 --> 00:27:34,320
I guess she only lets her guard down
around me.

398
00:27:41,460 --> 00:27:43,290
She tends to try to be cheerful, though.

399
00:27:43,930 --> 00:27:45,800
Maybe it's because
she's comfortable with me.

400
00:27:47,470 --> 00:27:48,700
That doesn't sound like her.

401
00:27:50,170 --> 00:27:51,940
So what did you think of Kim Jin Ju?

402
00:27:52,700 --> 00:27:54,540
I'm not good at getting a read on women.

403
00:27:55,370 --> 00:27:56,840
Don't you guys look at a woman's face?

404
00:27:57,340 --> 00:27:59,310
I don't pay close attention
if I don't have a reason to.

405
00:27:59,910 --> 00:28:01,710
So he wasn't interested in the slightest?

406
00:28:03,450 --> 00:28:04,750
She once...

407
00:28:05,420 --> 00:28:06,720
mentioned you to me.

408
00:28:07,620 --> 00:28:10,220
- What'd she say?
- That you're considerate.

409
00:28:11,120 --> 00:28:12,820
She said you even gave her money
for her taxi.

410
00:28:12,920 --> 00:28:15,330
Women must be born with amazing memories.

411
00:28:15,490 --> 00:28:18,830
We don't forget things that leave a mark,
either good or bad.

412
00:28:19,260 --> 00:28:20,630
Should I ask Ba Ra to come out?

413
00:28:21,170 --> 00:28:23,430
- Are you uncomfortable?
- No.

414
00:28:24,070 --> 00:28:26,140
Three's more fun than two,
don't you think?

415
00:28:27,440 --> 00:28:29,110
Should we invite her for a second round?

416
00:28:33,810 --> 00:28:35,650
I might as well rub it in
right in front of her face.

417
00:28:36,080 --> 00:28:37,720
The phone is turned off...

418
00:28:38,150 --> 00:28:39,150
It's off.

419
00:28:39,820 --> 00:28:41,420
She's always has it turned off these days.

420
00:28:41,650 --> 00:28:44,320
She probably keeps getting work calls
from people who don't know she's on leave.

421
00:28:49,930 --> 00:28:51,560
Let's just crash her place.

422
00:28:54,770 --> 00:28:56,030
She might have gone to bed early.

423
00:29:01,440 --> 00:29:05,010
- Sorry, the shoot ran late.
- What shoot?

424
00:29:05,280 --> 00:29:06,740
What's next?
Are you making your acting debut now?

425
00:29:06,810 --> 00:29:10,410
A magazine shoot for Choi Hoon,
so I had to be there.

426
00:29:11,780 --> 00:29:12,950
Your brother is here.

427
00:29:13,380 --> 00:29:14,390
Ha Yong Joong?

428
00:29:14,720 --> 00:29:16,690
- Yes.
- Who's he with?

429
00:29:16,890 --> 00:29:17,890
With Momo.

430
00:29:18,490 --> 00:29:19,490
Momo?

431
00:29:20,390 --> 00:29:21,390
The Momo?

432
00:29:24,760 --> 00:29:26,760
Let's get drinks next time
for a proper cheer me up.

433
00:29:26,760 --> 00:29:27,830
Okay.

434
00:29:31,770 --> 00:29:32,870
Hey, James.

435
00:29:33,340 --> 00:29:34,740
Mr. Ha!

436
00:29:35,040 --> 00:29:36,240
I heard you two were here.

437
00:29:36,740 --> 00:29:39,240
- I'm with Park Ho.
- Oh, Park Ho.

438
00:29:40,240 --> 00:29:41,450
Mind if we join you?

439
00:29:41,750 --> 00:29:42,750
Of course.

440
00:29:44,950 --> 00:29:46,480
He's the son of the CEO
of Hanik Pharmaceuticals,

441
00:29:46,780 --> 00:29:47,890
and he's a huge fan of yours.

442
00:29:49,050 --> 00:29:50,220
I see...

443
00:29:54,590 --> 00:29:56,090
How pathetic.

444
00:29:56,690 --> 00:29:59,000
- I should probably get going.
- Why?

445
00:30:00,030 --> 00:30:01,400
I'd just be in the way.

446
00:30:01,400 --> 00:30:03,070
What do you mean? He's a huge fan.

447
00:30:03,200 --> 00:30:04,440
He's like family to us.

448
00:30:04,500 --> 00:30:07,000
He's also really well-connected.
It's good to know him.

449
00:30:11,610 --> 00:30:12,880
Hey, it's been a while.

450
00:30:12,880 --> 00:30:14,880
Tell me about it. Not since
you've become a huge success.

451
00:30:14,950 --> 00:30:17,480
- Come on.
- You're a total icon these days.

452
00:30:17,550 --> 00:30:18,720
Those are baseless rumors.

453
00:30:19,480 --> 00:30:20,790
Even my twins...

454
00:30:23,450 --> 00:30:26,020
What? I look a little better, don't I?

455
00:30:26,720 --> 00:30:29,030
- You got the fat redistributed?
- Yes.

456
00:30:30,760 --> 00:30:31,760
Momo.

457
00:30:32,100 --> 00:30:33,700
Goodness, it's truly an honor.

458
00:30:34,370 --> 00:30:35,430
May I have a handshake?

459
00:30:38,370 --> 00:30:40,840
You're even prettier in person.

460
00:30:40,840 --> 00:30:42,110
Thank you.

461
00:30:49,080 --> 00:30:51,720
- Why aren't you heading home?
- Are you two dating already?

462
00:30:52,480 --> 00:30:53,750
What are you talking about?

463
00:30:54,020 --> 00:30:55,750
Stop dodging the question and sit down.

464
00:30:56,920 --> 00:30:58,320
I was just getting some water.

465
00:31:00,730 --> 00:31:01,990
I'll have ice water.

466
00:31:14,110 --> 00:31:15,140
(Discovery of the Mind)

467
00:31:19,740 --> 00:31:21,580
Let's just see each other once in a while,

468
00:31:22,450 --> 00:31:23,780
grab a meal, talk,

469
00:31:24,620 --> 00:31:26,280
and raise a baby together like that.

470
00:31:34,230 --> 00:31:35,960
What do you call it if not a date?
It was just the two of you.

471
00:31:36,260 --> 00:31:37,530
The same with Momo.

472
00:31:37,530 --> 00:31:39,960
She just called off her engagement.
And with you, of all people.

473
00:31:40,100 --> 00:31:41,900
She just sees me as an older brother.

474
00:31:41,900 --> 00:31:43,430
An older brother?

475
00:31:43,570 --> 00:31:45,940
But that's not you, right?

476
00:31:47,070 --> 00:31:49,170
We just had a meal.
Don't read too much into it.

477
00:31:49,240 --> 00:31:50,540
Not all meals are the same.

478
00:31:50,810 --> 00:31:52,780
With me, it would've just been a meal.

479
00:31:52,910 --> 00:31:54,750
Imagine how pathetic you'd look
if Ju Shin found out.

480
00:31:54,880 --> 00:31:58,220
- It's not like we're strangers.
- That's all the more reason.

481
00:31:58,680 --> 00:31:59,950
You need to keep your distance.

482
00:32:03,790 --> 00:32:05,620
At the end of the day,
you're just another guy.

483
00:32:06,060 --> 00:32:08,560
Smitten by a young, pretty face
and can't think straight.

484
00:32:08,960 --> 00:32:10,930
Do you really want to insult
your own brother like that?

485
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:13,730
- Am I wrong?
- It's not what you say, but your tone.

486
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:15,500
If you were me, would you ignore it?

487
00:32:15,630 --> 00:32:17,230
Her mom died so suddenly,

488
00:32:17,300 --> 00:32:19,870
- her stylist died, she called it off...
- She was the one...

489
00:32:19,940 --> 00:32:21,210
who ended the engagement.

490
00:32:21,270 --> 00:32:24,580
Her stylist's dad, on an ankle monitor,
suddenly blocked her car.

491
00:32:24,640 --> 00:32:25,680
How could she not be terrified?

492
00:32:26,840 --> 00:32:29,450
Look, whatever the reason,
just stay away from her.

493
00:32:29,680 --> 00:32:33,580
If a man and woman see each other often,
they're bound to catch feelings.

494
00:32:34,750 --> 00:32:37,960
I read your article.
Your writing is very concise and good.

495
00:32:38,590 --> 00:32:40,690
- You read it?
- Of course. Why wouldn't I?

496
00:32:41,830 --> 00:32:44,260
You turned our short chat
into an "exclusive interview."

497
00:32:46,530 --> 00:32:48,100
Ever thought about being an author?

498
00:32:49,100 --> 00:32:51,600
I think you have the talent for it.

499
00:32:51,740 --> 00:32:54,010
The Russian author,
Nikolay Karamzin, said that...

500
00:32:54,540 --> 00:32:56,710
writing portrays the soul and the heart,

501
00:32:56,970 --> 00:32:59,210
so a bad person
can never be a good writer.

502
00:32:59,910 --> 00:33:01,410
Does that mean you're a bad person?

503
00:33:03,210 --> 00:33:04,220
You're not.

504
00:33:04,650 --> 00:33:05,920
How would you know?

505
00:33:08,520 --> 00:33:11,760
- Here is our signature burger.
- Thank you.

506
00:33:12,160 --> 00:33:13,460
A burger's not complete without a Cola.

507
00:33:14,260 --> 00:33:15,330
I'll have one, then.

508
00:33:16,090 --> 00:33:17,090
With ice?

509
00:33:17,090 --> 00:33:19,260
- Yes.
- Me too, please.

510
00:33:22,900 --> 00:33:23,900
You're an F, right?

511
00:33:24,970 --> 00:33:26,440
And you're a T, aren't you?

512
00:33:26,640 --> 00:33:28,910
I don't know. I've never taken it.

513
00:33:29,570 --> 00:33:30,880
Do you want to take it now?

514
00:33:32,510 --> 00:33:33,680
It's beneath my dignity.

515
00:33:34,350 --> 00:33:36,850
To be defined by a test
someone else created.

516
00:33:37,620 --> 00:33:40,550
You're right.
My results change every time I take it.

517
00:33:43,450 --> 00:33:45,490
Do you really think you're a bad person?

518
00:33:49,260 --> 00:33:51,260
I don't feel like I'm a good person.

519
00:33:51,260 --> 00:33:52,960
As long as you don't feel
like a bad person, it's fine.

520
00:33:54,130 --> 00:33:55,230
It means you have a conscience.

521
00:33:56,670 --> 00:33:58,340
You're just being considerate.

522
00:33:58,970 --> 00:34:00,770
I have no reason to be considerate.

523
00:34:02,540 --> 00:34:05,480
Name one reason you think you're
a bad person.

524
00:34:07,280 --> 00:34:09,980
There are too many to name just one.

525
00:34:12,950 --> 00:34:14,020
Is it because of your job?

526
00:34:14,990 --> 00:34:16,550
Are all reporters that slick?

527
00:34:17,390 --> 00:34:18,890
Like a fox, to put it bluntly?

528
00:34:21,430 --> 00:34:23,060
You don't show your true colors,
is that it?

529
00:34:23,830 --> 00:34:25,530
It's always, "Director Shin."

530
00:34:26,760 --> 00:34:28,200
You're polite,
but it feels like you don't trust me.

531
00:34:29,970 --> 00:34:31,400
Are you an untrustworthy person?

532
00:34:32,140 --> 00:34:33,140
No.

533
00:34:33,670 --> 00:34:36,570
To be honest,
I'm trying not to cross any lines,

534
00:34:36,640 --> 00:34:39,280
so I'm always on my toes
and keeping my guard up.

535
00:34:39,610 --> 00:34:41,110
You don't seem tense at all.

536
00:34:42,150 --> 00:34:43,180
Are you playing poker?

537
00:34:44,450 --> 00:34:45,880
Are you saying I have a poker face?

538
00:34:46,820 --> 00:34:47,890
Now I'm curious...

539
00:34:48,650 --> 00:34:50,620
to see what happens
when you're not so focused...

540
00:34:51,060 --> 00:34:52,460
and finally cross that line.

541
00:34:53,590 --> 00:34:55,990
You might not want to see me ever again.

542
00:34:57,290 --> 00:34:58,530
Go on, try me.

543
00:34:59,500 --> 00:35:01,500
So you'll let it slide
no matter what I do?

544
00:35:06,770 --> 00:35:08,470
I really shouldn't.

545
00:35:15,580 --> 00:35:17,720
(Nikolay)

546
00:35:20,180 --> 00:35:21,290
(Nikolay Karamzin)

547
00:35:22,290 --> 00:35:24,790
(A Russian writer, poet,
historian, and critic)

548
00:35:28,160 --> 00:35:29,160
Anyway...

549
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:32,700
Don't change your mind about this.

550
00:35:33,600 --> 00:35:36,800
I didn't think Momo was like that,
but I guess her true colors are showing.

551
00:35:37,770 --> 00:35:39,300
Worry about yourself.

552
00:35:42,070 --> 00:35:45,940
You always understood me and had my back,
even when I dropped out.

553
00:35:46,910 --> 00:35:48,450
If it were anyone else,

554
00:35:48,450 --> 00:35:51,550
I wouldn't care if they dated a single mom
or some middle-aged divorcée.

555
00:35:51,880 --> 00:35:53,350
What have I got to worry about?

556
00:35:54,590 --> 00:35:56,390
Honestly, I've had this thought.

557
00:35:56,920 --> 00:36:00,360
That you don't intend to get married
and just fake interest in women,

558
00:36:00,420 --> 00:36:01,930
like you're just stringing them along.

559
00:36:02,490 --> 00:36:06,030
- I sometimes think that.
- String them along? Don't be ridiculous.

560
00:36:08,600 --> 00:36:10,300
You brought it up, so spit it out.

561
00:36:12,770 --> 00:36:14,040
What worries me is that...

562
00:36:15,370 --> 00:36:18,410
maybe you lack confidence as a man.

563
00:36:24,220 --> 00:36:25,320
You mean...

564
00:36:26,020 --> 00:36:27,690
that there's something wrong with me
down there?

565
00:36:28,350 --> 00:36:30,120
No, I mean mentally.

566
00:36:31,690 --> 00:36:32,820
Unbelievable.

567
00:36:33,490 --> 00:36:35,660
Ha Yong Joong,
you're the one with the problem.

568
00:36:35,930 --> 00:36:37,960
People are a product of their environment.

569
00:36:38,030 --> 00:36:39,600
And I mostly work with women.

570
00:36:39,660 --> 00:36:42,600
My employees, actresses, reporters,
all those society wives.

571
00:36:42,670 --> 00:36:45,300
I'm telling you, it just looks like
your interest in women is superficial.

572
00:36:45,370 --> 00:36:48,610
- I've been consumed by work. You know.
- And you think I haven't?

573
00:36:48,910 --> 00:36:51,740
Babies are born even in wartime.
All it takes is the will.

574
00:36:52,280 --> 00:36:54,110
You've never brought anyone home.

575
00:36:54,250 --> 00:36:55,410
Never even introduced me to anyone.

576
00:36:55,480 --> 00:36:57,180
I need to feel that forever spark.

577
00:36:57,180 --> 00:36:59,350
What can I do if I haven't found her yet?

578
00:37:01,250 --> 00:37:02,550
The last thing that worries me is...

579
00:37:03,950 --> 00:37:05,120
that instead of women,

580
00:37:05,660 --> 00:37:06,820
you like men.

581
00:37:06,890 --> 00:37:07,990
Why you...

582
00:37:10,360 --> 00:37:12,360
I'd have an easier time understanding
if you just said you liked Ba Ra.

583
00:37:12,430 --> 00:37:15,230
Ba Ra is like a daughter to me,
if I'm being a little dramatic.

584
00:37:16,000 --> 00:37:18,640
For Mom and Dad's sake,
stay on the straight and narrow.

585
00:37:19,840 --> 00:37:22,510
- Mom might have understood.
- Ha Yong Joong.

586
00:37:22,570 --> 00:37:24,710
I was just throwing it out there.
Don't worry.

587
00:37:26,410 --> 00:37:31,280
For all our loyal listeners tuning in,
you're in for a big surprise.

588
00:37:31,350 --> 00:37:34,650
That's right,
today's special guest is Momo!

589
00:37:35,950 --> 00:37:38,260
Could you please say hello
to our dear listeners?

590
00:37:38,460 --> 00:37:39,820
Hello. This is Jin...

591
00:37:39,890 --> 00:37:40,920
(This is Jin Ju.)

592
00:37:42,730 --> 00:37:45,830
I've been wanting to come on for a while.
I'm glad you finally invited me.

593
00:37:46,230 --> 00:37:50,600
- It's Momo.
- Wait, weren't you already invited?

594
00:37:51,470 --> 00:37:53,200
Was I misinformed?

595
00:37:53,700 --> 00:37:55,110
The message never got to me...

596
00:37:56,170 --> 00:37:58,580
Well, either way,
it's an honor to have you here.

597
00:37:59,080 --> 00:38:00,080
Thank you.

598
00:38:02,880 --> 00:38:06,220
As a game developer, have you
ever thought about that kind of problem?

599
00:38:06,720 --> 00:38:09,190
Of course. I used to be addicted myself.

600
00:38:09,190 --> 00:38:10,990
How old were you when you first played?

601
00:38:11,290 --> 00:38:13,520
In elementary school,
my parents were strict,

602
00:38:13,720 --> 00:38:16,230
so I only played for short, set times.

603
00:38:16,360 --> 00:38:17,530
Was it like a whole new world?

604
00:38:17,530 --> 00:38:20,860
Yes. I got really hooked in high school.

605
00:38:21,370 --> 00:38:23,730
And that's ultimately why
I ended up dropping out.

606
00:38:23,800 --> 00:38:26,400
That's a topic our listeners
are very curious about.

607
00:38:26,400 --> 00:38:29,570
They're flooding our text line right now.

608
00:38:29,570 --> 00:38:30,710
(Ryu Ju Hyun's Connect Today.)

609
00:38:30,710 --> 00:38:32,080
(Is this a game or a form of gambling?)

610
00:38:32,840 --> 00:38:34,310
They're almost all complaints.

611
00:38:35,310 --> 00:38:39,420
When can we expect to see you
in a drama or movie again, Momo?

612
00:38:43,190 --> 00:38:44,960
It might be a while...

613
00:38:45,820 --> 00:38:49,090
With my mom gone,
I've lost a lot of my confidence.

614
00:38:50,560 --> 00:38:53,000
As a fan, I'm sad to hear that,
but I completely understand.

615
00:38:53,400 --> 00:38:56,430
A hobby might help at a time like this.

616
00:38:56,430 --> 00:38:57,600
What about scuba diving?

617
00:38:57,670 --> 00:38:58,700
I gave it up.

618
00:39:00,240 --> 00:39:02,710
I really have to ask this next question.

619
00:39:02,810 --> 00:39:06,780
Many people are sad about what happened
with you and Director Shin Ju Shin...

620
00:39:06,840 --> 00:39:09,380
and are hoping you two
might get back together.

621
00:39:10,980 --> 00:39:12,920
He deserves someone better than me.

622
00:39:14,420 --> 00:39:16,450
Do you believe in things like fate?

623
00:39:24,860 --> 00:39:25,860
How was I?

624
00:39:26,160 --> 00:39:27,230
Later...

625
00:39:28,430 --> 00:39:30,170
CEO Ha is on that other show.

626
00:39:30,230 --> 00:39:33,200
- Really? CEO Ha?
- Yes, there he is.

627
00:39:40,280 --> 00:39:42,450
- What show were you on?
- Hello.

628
00:39:45,950 --> 00:39:47,420
"Ryu Ju Hyun's Connect Today."

629
00:39:48,190 --> 00:39:50,950
We're heading out for dinner.
Do you have any plans?

630
00:39:51,520 --> 00:39:52,520
No.

631
00:39:53,120 --> 00:39:54,860
Great. Then you can join us.

632
00:39:56,290 --> 00:39:57,390
Is anyone else joining you?

633
00:39:57,930 --> 00:40:00,700
No. Tell the restaurant
one more person is coming.

634
00:40:04,170 --> 00:40:05,900
You do radio shows too?

635
00:40:05,900 --> 00:40:07,400
It was a request related to my game,

636
00:40:08,040 --> 00:40:10,870
and I wanted to explain a few things.

637
00:40:11,010 --> 00:40:12,040
Yes.

638
00:40:12,340 --> 00:40:13,540
Yes, thank you.

639
00:40:20,620 --> 00:40:21,650
Shall we go?

640
00:40:30,490 --> 00:40:32,930
- Where's Pickles?
- He's at James' place.

641
00:40:33,300 --> 00:40:35,270
- Did my brother call you?
- Yes.

642
00:40:35,870 --> 00:40:37,800
I'm sorry for bothering you.

643
00:40:37,800 --> 00:40:38,970
Not at all.

644
00:40:39,200 --> 00:40:41,310
Does Yong Joong know you're here?

645
00:40:41,770 --> 00:40:44,880
I didn't tell him. He's always so busy...

646
00:40:47,680 --> 00:40:50,710
Was there something
you wanted to talk about?

647
00:40:55,020 --> 00:40:58,560
- We're hitting rush hour traffic.
- It'll be an hour at most.

648
00:41:01,290 --> 00:41:02,390
Okay, see you in a bit then.

649
00:41:02,660 --> 00:41:03,690
Okay.

650
00:41:03,960 --> 00:41:05,700
Why don't you just ride with us?

651
00:41:06,430 --> 00:41:07,760
I drove my own car here.

652
00:41:08,370 --> 00:41:09,800
You don't have any other stops to make,
do you?

653
00:41:10,270 --> 00:41:11,270
No, I don't.

654
00:41:27,320 --> 00:41:30,750
- Find the show CEO Ha was on.
- It might not be airing yet.

655
00:41:30,820 --> 00:41:31,960
I did okay, right?

656
00:41:32,320 --> 00:41:33,320
Yes.

657
00:41:35,060 --> 00:41:36,060
What's wrong?

658
00:41:38,200 --> 00:41:41,630
Earlier, when the DJ said
it was an honor to have you,

659
00:41:41,830 --> 00:41:44,100
you should have said,
"No, the honor is all mine."

660
00:41:44,740 --> 00:41:47,940
He's much older than you
and has been in broadcasting for decades.

661
00:41:48,310 --> 00:41:50,010
He's a pretty big deal himself.

662
00:41:59,950 --> 00:42:03,850
By any chance, have you ever heard
Yong Joong talk about Momo?

663
00:42:05,190 --> 00:42:07,790
- Yes. I have.
- So you know about Yong Joong?

664
00:42:09,090 --> 00:42:10,130
Yes.

665
00:42:12,000 --> 00:42:13,930
I'm so worried something might happen
between them.

666
00:42:14,000 --> 00:42:15,500
Why did she have to cancel the engagement?

667
00:42:16,970 --> 00:42:18,400
What's your take on it?

668
00:42:18,600 --> 00:42:19,670
Do you think they're a good match?

669
00:42:21,070 --> 00:42:22,210
In terms of looks, yes.

670
00:42:22,510 --> 00:42:23,740
No, I mean their circumstances.

671
00:42:24,510 --> 00:42:26,840
She was his friend's fiancée,
which everyone knows.

672
00:42:30,880 --> 00:42:33,420
"Keep chipping away,
and it's sure to fall."

673
00:42:34,380 --> 00:42:37,850
What if Yong Joong makes a move
and she gives in?

674
00:42:39,890 --> 00:42:42,130
Can't you do something to keep them apart?

675
00:42:45,500 --> 00:42:46,930
It makes me really nervous.

676
00:42:48,200 --> 00:42:50,300
I already had a firm talk with my brother,

677
00:42:51,400 --> 00:42:53,370
but you never know
when it comes to men and women.

678
00:42:55,240 --> 00:42:57,110
You're a really great public speaker.

679
00:42:57,610 --> 00:42:58,610
So you listened to the broadcast?

680
00:42:58,880 --> 00:43:00,840
- On our way here.
- We'll have the tasting course.

681
00:43:00,910 --> 00:43:01,910
Yes, sir.

682
00:43:05,650 --> 00:43:07,320
I couldn't stop asking myself today...

683
00:43:08,420 --> 00:43:12,020
if the game I made was ruining these kids

684
00:43:12,620 --> 00:43:13,790
What are you talking about?

685
00:43:14,490 --> 00:43:16,690
I was flooded
with angry messages from parents.

686
00:43:17,290 --> 00:43:18,930
They said their kids
were losing interest in their studies.

687
00:43:19,730 --> 00:43:21,570
You can't let every single one of those
get to you.

688
00:43:22,730 --> 00:43:24,400
But I'm supposed to be
a positive force in the world.

689
00:43:25,400 --> 00:43:26,940
That's what my parents taught me.

690
00:43:28,040 --> 00:43:30,340
They were truly wonderful people,
both of them.

691
00:43:31,310 --> 00:43:35,510
If my kid were ignoring their studies
for some all-consuming game,

692
00:43:36,680 --> 00:43:38,080
I'd be really upset.

693
00:43:38,080 --> 00:43:39,820
But how is game addiction your fault?

694
00:43:40,620 --> 00:43:41,650
I made the game.

695
00:43:41,950 --> 00:43:44,760
Games themselves are fun
and a good way to relieve stress.

696
00:43:45,160 --> 00:43:46,290
It's the addiction that's the problem.

697
00:43:46,620 --> 00:43:49,560
Even without your game,
how many other addictive things are there?

698
00:43:50,330 --> 00:43:53,500
And if you stopped making them,
would games just disappear?

699
00:43:56,100 --> 00:43:59,870
People get addicted to food,
not to mention alcohol and coffee.

700
00:44:00,500 --> 00:44:04,070
Do you see anyone blaming the farmers
or the coffee producers?

701
00:44:04,740 --> 00:44:06,880
We need to eat to live.

702
00:44:07,010 --> 00:44:08,450
The problem is eating too much.

703
00:44:08,910 --> 00:44:11,010
Carb addiction, alcoholism.

704
00:44:11,450 --> 00:44:14,850
It's up to everyone to use self-control.
You have nothing to feel guilty about.

705
00:44:15,820 --> 00:44:16,820
She's right.

706
00:44:20,320 --> 00:44:22,090
Like you said on the air today,

707
00:44:22,430 --> 00:44:25,260
the game you developed
is way less violent.

708
00:44:28,130 --> 00:44:31,070
Plus, it has a great story
with a clear theme of good defeating evil.

709
00:44:31,400 --> 00:44:33,640
When you're done playing,
it makes you want to be a better person.

710
00:44:35,310 --> 00:44:36,610
That's what I was going for.
You really felt that?

711
00:44:37,070 --> 00:44:38,080
Definitely.

712
00:44:40,110 --> 00:44:41,710
That makes me feel a little better.

713
00:44:43,080 --> 00:44:44,450
You don't have any addictions, do you?

714
00:44:47,620 --> 00:44:49,650
I'm addicted to people.

715
00:44:52,320 --> 00:44:53,520
Good people.

716
00:44:56,260 --> 00:44:57,460
I hope I'm one of them.

717
00:44:58,660 --> 00:45:00,100
You get plenty of love as it is.

718
00:45:18,380 --> 00:45:19,380
Reporter Geum.

719
00:45:30,460 --> 00:45:33,460
To celebrate a successful show,
let's all have a drink tonight.

720
00:45:42,240 --> 00:45:43,870
(Momo)

721
00:45:43,940 --> 00:45:46,340
When were done drinking,
make sure Ba Ra gets home safe.

722
00:45:47,340 --> 00:45:48,350
Got it.

723
00:45:50,350 --> 00:45:51,450
You know, a man...

724
00:45:51,820 --> 00:45:53,420
can have an easy life...

725
00:45:53,550 --> 00:45:57,090
if he just listens to his mother,
his wife, and the woman on the GPS.

726
00:45:58,390 --> 00:45:59,720
My mom passed away,

727
00:46:00,520 --> 00:46:03,760
so I guess I just have to listen to my GPS
and Ba Ra.

728
00:46:09,730 --> 00:46:10,730
Let's drink while it's cold.

729
00:46:21,210 --> 00:46:24,510
Don't you want to hear me sing tonight?

730
00:46:29,020 --> 00:46:30,020
I'd love to.

731
00:46:42,200 --> 00:46:43,200
Pace yourself.

732
00:46:47,500 --> 00:46:48,810
I just want to get drunk fast.

733
00:46:49,140 --> 00:46:50,140
Why?

734
00:46:55,350 --> 00:46:57,650
Perfect. Get drunk and duck out early.

735
00:47:00,150 --> 00:47:02,020
I might as well too,
since I have both of you here tonight.

736
00:47:07,720 --> 00:47:08,730
Ba Ra.

737
00:47:19,800 --> 00:47:21,170
Have you ever been to karaoke with him?

738
00:47:21,870 --> 00:47:24,040
I've actually never heard her sing.

739
00:47:24,910 --> 00:47:26,080
You're better off not.

740
00:47:27,140 --> 00:47:28,140
It's just noise pollution.

741
00:47:32,020 --> 00:47:34,580
Is the chef still from Australia?

742
00:47:34,580 --> 00:47:35,650
Yes.

743
00:47:51,740 --> 00:47:52,740
What's wrong?

744
00:47:58,780 --> 00:48:00,840
- Tell Momo to come out here.
- Okay.

745
00:48:04,380 --> 00:48:05,380
Momo...

746
00:48:07,480 --> 00:48:09,290
Eat your steak while it's hot.

747
00:48:13,690 --> 00:48:14,930
Here you go.

748
00:48:15,330 --> 00:48:17,160
- Is it organic?
- Of course.

749
00:48:17,490 --> 00:48:19,930
I only feed my daughter organic steak.

750
00:48:23,500 --> 00:48:24,830
This reminds me of my mom...

751
00:48:25,800 --> 00:48:27,840
She always used to cut my steak for me.

752
00:48:28,640 --> 00:48:29,910
She said my hands were too weak.

753
00:48:33,180 --> 00:48:35,180
- Let me.
- No, it's okay.

754
00:49:13,420 --> 00:49:14,620
Thank you.

755
00:49:21,120 --> 00:49:22,130
Want me to cut yours?

756
00:49:24,190 --> 00:49:25,200
I'm good.

757
00:49:27,060 --> 00:49:28,930
You must be too happy to even eat.

758
00:49:30,370 --> 00:49:32,000
Not a care in the world...

759
00:49:33,200 --> 00:49:35,140
with a guy like CEO Ha watching your back.

760
00:49:39,980 --> 00:49:41,180
He's not my actual brother, though.

761
00:49:42,010 --> 00:49:44,310
Plenty of real brothers
are worse than strangers.

762
00:49:44,780 --> 00:49:45,980
Take Manager Mimi from my salon,
for instance.

763
00:49:46,520 --> 00:49:48,790
She said her older brother beat her
until she finished elementary school.

764
00:49:50,020 --> 00:49:51,090
How could he hit his own sister?

765
00:49:51,450 --> 00:49:52,460
I know, right?

766
00:49:52,920 --> 00:49:54,260
Something's wrong with him.

767
00:49:56,630 --> 00:49:57,630
(New text message)

768
00:50:00,130 --> 00:50:01,460
They booked a karaoke room for us.

769
00:50:02,230 --> 00:50:04,200
I already asked a friend to set one up.

770
00:50:04,470 --> 00:50:05,600
Really?

771
00:50:08,810 --> 00:50:09,810
Feeling any better?

772
00:50:10,740 --> 00:50:13,040
Yes, a little.

773
00:50:13,440 --> 00:50:15,450
If you'd gone to the ER,
you wouldn't have been seen right away.

774
00:50:16,110 --> 00:50:17,650
They would've run all kinds
of tests on you,

775
00:50:17,910 --> 00:50:19,180
and you'd be on medication
for over ten days.

776
00:50:20,520 --> 00:50:21,820
Did you have a good dream last night?

777
00:50:22,350 --> 00:50:23,350
No.

778
00:50:25,520 --> 00:50:26,920
All right, sit up straight.

779
00:50:27,860 --> 00:50:28,860
Slowly.

780
00:50:35,500 --> 00:50:37,400
Don't shower tonight.
Just sleep as you are.

781
00:50:38,000 --> 00:50:39,000
Just take off your outerwear.

782
00:50:39,770 --> 00:50:40,800
You shouldn't be moving around.

783
00:50:43,670 --> 00:50:46,680
I thought you only specialized
in neurosurgery.

784
00:50:50,410 --> 00:50:51,580
I can even deliver a baby.

785
00:50:52,380 --> 00:50:53,450
Try to find something I can't do.

786
00:50:56,350 --> 00:50:57,450
Get some rest,

787
00:50:57,850 --> 00:50:59,690
and be careful. It's known to relapse.

788
00:51:01,960 --> 00:51:03,060
Director Shin.

789
00:51:06,700 --> 00:51:07,700
Yes?

790
00:51:08,230 --> 00:51:09,430
Thank you.

791
00:51:10,570 --> 00:51:11,570
I mean it.

792
00:51:17,670 --> 00:51:20,340
<i>In the quiet of the evening</i>

793
00:51:21,540 --> 00:51:24,380
<i>When the city lights grow dim</i>

794
00:51:24,450 --> 00:51:27,720
<i>I feel the rhythm in your heartbeat</i>

795
00:51:28,420 --> 00:51:31,390
<i>Pulling me close again</i>

796
00:51:31,690 --> 00:51:34,020
<i>And every step we're taking</i>

797
00:51:34,020 --> 00:51:39,330
<i>Feels like time is slowing down</i>

798
00:51:41,700 --> 00:51:44,470
<i>So hold me in this moment</i>

799
00:51:44,600 --> 00:51:47,570
<i>Where the world just fades away</i>

800
00:51:47,640 --> 00:51:50,740
<i>Let the blues keep playing</i>

801
00:51:50,870 --> 00:51:53,840
<i>Got a feeling we're dancing</i>

802
00:51:53,980 --> 00:51:57,310
<i>With you I feel the old-time magic</i>

803
00:51:57,550 --> 00:52:00,650
<i>Like a record softly spinning</i>

804
00:52:00,980 --> 00:52:04,450
<i>And I'm falling</i>

805
00:52:04,690 --> 00:52:10,630
<i>Falling all over again</i>

806
00:52:23,770 --> 00:52:24,770
Yong Joong.

807
00:52:54,940 --> 00:52:57,910
<i>Sometimes he says too much</i>

808
00:52:59,240 --> 00:53:02,080
<i>Sometimes nothing at all</i>

809
00:53:04,380 --> 00:53:06,550
<i>But I've seen his heart</i>

810
00:53:07,220 --> 00:53:08,220
What do you want to sing?

811
00:53:09,220 --> 00:53:12,190
- I'm a horrible singer.
- That's okay. I'm a great listener.

812
00:53:12,420 --> 00:53:14,090
I'm better as a backup dancer.

813
00:53:14,420 --> 00:53:17,490
- Dancing?
<i>- I won't walk away</i>

814
00:53:17,560 --> 00:53:20,160
<i>- Through the long night</i>
- You should be the one singing.

815
00:53:20,630 --> 00:53:24,730
<i>I'll hold your hand when it ain't right</i>

816
00:53:25,400 --> 00:53:26,600
<i>It's love</i>

817
00:53:30,210 --> 00:53:33,910
- What gives? How rude.
- It must be an important call.

818
00:53:48,990 --> 00:53:50,530
What's wrong? Are you dizzy?

819
00:53:52,300 --> 00:53:55,630
(Shin Ju Shin, Director of Neurosurgery)

820
00:54:02,740 --> 00:54:04,240
(Geum Ba Ra)

821
00:54:06,580 --> 00:54:07,910
- Yes.
- Director Shin,

822
00:54:07,910 --> 00:54:10,280
we're at Silro Hotel karaoke.
Can you come here?

823
00:54:10,810 --> 00:54:12,250
- I'm on my way.
- Okay.

824
00:54:12,380 --> 00:54:16,150
(Nua General Hospital)

825
00:54:18,290 --> 00:54:19,620
Mr. Chairman. Good evening.

826
00:54:23,830 --> 00:54:25,330
How long ago did he collapse?

827
00:54:30,670 --> 00:54:33,270
It's vertigo. Director Shin's coming.

828
00:54:33,270 --> 00:54:34,300
Ju Shin is?

829
00:54:34,440 --> 00:54:35,610
We should call 911.

830
00:54:35,610 --> 00:54:37,170
No, Director Shin
can treat her right away.

831
00:54:37,470 --> 00:54:38,570
I feel nauseous.

832
00:54:39,280 --> 00:54:40,540
I think I'm going to throw up.

833
00:54:48,950 --> 00:54:50,120
It could be a vascular issue.

834
00:54:51,520 --> 00:54:52,520
Are you dizzy?

835
00:54:52,960 --> 00:54:54,360
I can't even keep my eyes open.

836
00:54:55,120 --> 00:54:57,660
The same thing happened to me,
but Director Shin fixed it right away.

837
00:54:59,100 --> 00:55:01,030
- When?
- Not too long ago.

838
00:55:01,460 --> 00:55:02,500
Why didn't you tell me?

839
00:55:04,400 --> 00:55:05,400
Why?

840
00:55:05,840 --> 00:55:07,400
Because I got better right away.

841
00:55:13,910 --> 00:55:16,380
Even though I'm dizzy, this feeling...

842
00:55:23,490 --> 00:55:24,650
Are you sure he's coming?

843
00:55:27,920 --> 00:55:29,530
The person you are calling
is on another line...

844
00:55:30,060 --> 00:55:31,060
He's on the phone?

845
00:55:40,300 --> 00:55:42,410
Was there any slurred speech
or signs of paralysis?

846
00:55:44,640 --> 00:55:45,640
Okay.

847
00:55:51,010 --> 00:55:52,080
Yes, this is he.

848
00:55:52,250 --> 00:55:55,120
A stroke patient, Mr. Lee Han Jeong, 76,
will be arriving,

849
00:55:55,350 --> 00:55:56,790
so get him straight to an emergency MRI.

850
00:56:02,660 --> 00:56:05,090
Don't worry, Mr. Chairman.
The emergency team is on standby.

851
00:56:05,760 --> 00:56:06,860
I'll be there shortly too.

852
00:56:08,130 --> 00:56:09,130
Yes, sir.

853
00:56:11,270 --> 00:56:13,670
- Is the karaoke bar in the basement?
- Yes, it's in the basement.

854
00:56:17,470 --> 00:56:18,640
Director Shin!

855
00:56:20,980 --> 00:56:22,250
Yes, Reporter Hwang, hello.

856
00:56:22,750 --> 00:56:24,080
Yes, I enjoyed your latest article.

857
00:56:37,090 --> 00:56:38,260
I think it's vertigo.

858
00:56:44,930 --> 00:56:45,940
Hurry.

859
00:56:47,600 --> 00:56:49,470
- What was she doing?
- Singing.

860
00:56:59,180 --> 00:57:00,220
Call 911.

861
00:57:01,850 --> 00:57:03,190
Our ENT Department is full.

862
00:57:07,160 --> 00:57:08,620
I just got a call
about a critical patient.

863
00:57:10,490 --> 00:57:11,490
Call 911.

864
00:57:18,940 --> 00:57:20,140
That bastard.

865
00:57:21,000 --> 00:57:23,240
Did he rush here thinking it was Ba Ra,
or what?

866
00:57:24,570 --> 00:57:26,110
This is the Silro Hotel karaoke bar.

867
00:57:32,220 --> 00:57:34,250
The phone is turned off.

868
00:57:34,320 --> 00:57:37,220
Please leave a message after the tone.

869
00:57:37,220 --> 00:57:39,190
(Momo)

870
00:57:47,260 --> 00:57:51,070
Only one guardian's allowed in the ER,
so you should go home.

871
00:57:53,170 --> 00:57:55,970
Don't worry. She'll be fine in no time,
just like I was.

872
00:57:57,170 --> 00:57:58,170
Who's coming with the patient?

873
00:57:59,640 --> 00:58:02,650
(Emergency Services)

874
00:58:21,260 --> 00:58:22,270
Hello?

875
00:58:22,930 --> 00:58:23,930
Are you with a patient?

876
00:58:24,400 --> 00:58:26,000
I just finished up.

877
00:58:26,240 --> 00:58:28,100
They said there was nothing
they could do for her in the ER.

878
00:58:28,370 --> 00:58:30,540
They said we have to wait
for the doctor tomorrow morning.

879
00:58:32,210 --> 00:58:34,940
- They didn't do an MRI, did they?
- I heard you could fix it right away.

880
00:58:35,210 --> 00:58:36,750
Ba Ra said you helped her
with her vertigo.

881
00:58:37,210 --> 00:58:38,210
Yes.

882
00:58:39,050 --> 00:58:40,050
So?

883
00:58:40,480 --> 00:58:42,120
The circumstances were different then.

884
00:58:42,620 --> 00:58:44,820
- You rushed all the way over just to...
- I told you I had a critical patient.

885
00:58:46,320 --> 00:58:47,920
Is that how little you care now?

886
00:58:47,990 --> 00:58:49,490
She'll feel better with some medicine.

887
00:58:50,890 --> 00:58:52,060
Is Ba Ra at the hospital?

888
00:58:52,730 --> 00:58:54,730
- Yes.
- Where?

889
00:58:55,260 --> 00:58:56,270
Unjin Hospital?

890
00:58:56,730 --> 00:58:59,470
Yes. Can't you call the ER for us?

891
00:58:59,540 --> 00:59:01,740
- To the doctor on duty?
- I'd get chewed out.

892
00:59:03,070 --> 00:59:04,870
Besides, there's nothing
the on-duty doctor can do.

893
00:59:05,340 --> 00:59:07,140
A doctor from the ENT Department
will be there first thing in the morning.

894
00:59:07,980 --> 00:59:09,610
She'll be fine as long as she lies still.

895
00:59:10,080 --> 00:59:11,410
You sound so detached.

896
00:59:12,420 --> 00:59:14,780
She was your fiancée, Momo.

897
00:59:14,780 --> 00:59:15,990
She was even carrying my child too.

898
00:59:18,390 --> 00:59:20,090
Emotionally, we're completely over.

899
00:59:20,760 --> 00:59:21,760
For both of us.

900
00:59:22,590 --> 00:59:23,630
Just like that?

901
00:59:24,390 --> 00:59:25,660
I'll try calling Geum Ba Ra.

902
00:59:34,470 --> 00:59:35,540
What took you so long to answer?

903
00:59:36,140 --> 00:59:37,510
I had to step out to take the call.

904
00:59:37,710 --> 00:59:39,780
I sent someone over,
so you can switch with them and go home.

905
00:59:41,280 --> 00:59:43,310
There's nothing more
you can do by staying.

906
00:59:43,910 --> 00:59:46,180
No, I need to be here.

907
00:59:46,920 --> 00:59:47,920
She's only Momo in body.

908
00:59:50,190 --> 00:59:52,150
If I were ever rushed to the ER,

909
00:59:53,520 --> 00:59:54,590
would you be by my side?

910
00:59:56,230 --> 00:59:57,230
Yes.

911
00:59:57,990 --> 00:59:59,000
And why is that?

912
01:00:00,530 --> 01:00:02,130
Like I'd ever get the chance?

913
01:00:02,470 --> 01:00:05,200
The hospital staff would be
hovering over you.

914
01:00:05,870 --> 01:00:07,970
So it was just lip service?

915
01:00:11,810 --> 01:00:12,810
Yes.

916
01:00:14,910 --> 01:00:16,980
Didn't I tell you being brutally honest
is rude and not a good look?

917
01:00:17,280 --> 01:00:18,710
You thought I was serious?

918
01:00:20,020 --> 01:00:23,050
Of course, I have to repay you
after everything you've done for me.

919
01:00:23,690 --> 01:00:25,020
I haven't personally
done anything for you.

920
01:00:26,090 --> 01:00:28,460
But thanks to you,
my vertigo was treated right away.

921
01:00:29,890 --> 01:00:30,990
So it's just to repay a debt?

922
01:00:35,100 --> 01:00:36,630
Does the reason matter?

923
01:00:36,800 --> 01:00:37,800
The intention is what matters.

924
01:00:38,830 --> 01:00:39,840
More than the reason.

925
01:00:42,040 --> 01:00:44,540
I'm always grateful. I really am.

926
01:00:45,070 --> 01:00:46,340
Then get rid of that feeling,
starting now.

927
01:00:47,640 --> 01:00:49,010
I'm not lacking for anything,

928
01:00:50,150 --> 01:00:51,410
and I'm tired of being thanked.

929
01:00:52,110 --> 01:00:54,080
I don't care for effort
born from obligation.

930
01:00:54,820 --> 01:00:57,190
- I'm not forcing myself.
- Regardless.

931
01:01:01,020 --> 01:01:02,560
Want me to look for a purebred Retriever?

932
01:01:05,590 --> 01:01:06,600
No.

933
01:01:09,830 --> 01:01:10,970
What about the critical patient?

934
01:01:11,300 --> 01:01:12,540
We got to them within the golden hour,

935
01:01:13,800 --> 01:01:14,800
so they should be fine.

936
01:01:16,340 --> 01:01:18,110
You must be exhausted.

937
01:01:18,670 --> 01:01:20,410
I don't know if I'm just breaking down
now that I'm over 30.

938
01:01:22,310 --> 01:01:23,880
But to be honest,
I was feeling a bit tired.

939
01:01:25,250 --> 01:01:26,250
But it's gone now.

940
01:01:27,150 --> 01:01:28,880
Did you see the moon that night?

941
01:01:29,790 --> 01:01:30,790
Pardon?

942
01:01:31,190 --> 01:01:32,190
Did you see it?

943
01:01:32,460 --> 01:01:33,690
Yes, I saw it.

944
01:01:34,820 --> 01:01:37,690
What do you say we talk on the phone
like this once a day?

945
01:01:39,300 --> 01:01:41,230
Would you even have the time?

946
01:01:42,030 --> 01:01:43,370
Don't phrase your refusal as a question.

947
01:01:44,070 --> 01:01:46,700
If your hands shake when you get older
and can't operate,

948
01:01:46,700 --> 01:01:48,840
switch to psychiatry.

949
01:01:50,170 --> 01:01:51,910
Ever seen a psychiatrist?

950
01:01:52,440 --> 01:01:53,440
No.

951
01:01:54,540 --> 01:01:55,540
Then see me.

952
01:01:56,050 --> 01:01:57,110
I'll be your personal doctor.

953
01:01:57,710 --> 01:01:58,710
Your all-in-one personal doctor.

954
01:01:59,520 --> 01:02:00,780
How about an MRI while we're at it?

955
01:02:02,180 --> 01:02:04,620
That's scary. Stop trying to scare me.

956
01:02:05,990 --> 01:02:07,320
Why are you afraid of so many things?

957
01:02:08,660 --> 01:02:09,860
You're scared of the rain, too.

958
01:02:10,930 --> 01:02:12,430
And yet you ran circles
around those detectives.

959
01:02:12,730 --> 01:02:15,060
That's just because I was
too naive to know any better.

960
01:02:18,000 --> 01:02:19,470
Are you a half-grown puppy now?

961
01:02:20,370 --> 01:02:21,670
Even when you get older,
don't become the tiger.

962
01:02:22,270 --> 01:02:23,710
Do people turn into tigers
when they get old?

963
01:02:24,040 --> 01:02:25,210
My mom used to say that.

964
01:02:26,080 --> 01:02:28,410
No, wait. I think I heard it from my dad.

965
01:02:30,010 --> 01:02:32,950
He said women start out as puppies
but turn into tigers as they age.

966
01:02:33,380 --> 01:02:36,720
You have times when your memory
isn't always perfect?

967
01:02:37,920 --> 01:02:40,520
Talking to you
makes me want to see your face.

968
01:02:42,190 --> 01:02:43,190
Should I come over?

969
01:02:46,800 --> 01:02:47,800
Or do you want to come here?

970
01:02:54,400 --> 01:02:57,770
Are you serious about coming over?

971
01:02:59,010 --> 01:03:00,210
You know I don't say things I don't mean.

972
01:03:01,710 --> 01:03:04,480
With your sterling character,
you can afford empty promises.

973
01:03:05,850 --> 01:03:06,850
My character?

974
01:03:07,150 --> 01:03:09,390
With your perfect resume,
family background, and character,

975
01:03:10,120 --> 01:03:12,620
adding a spoonful of empty promises
would make you absolutely perfect.

976
01:03:16,730 --> 01:03:18,960
All right. I'll work on it.

977
01:03:22,670 --> 01:03:23,670
Don't you...

978
01:03:24,470 --> 01:03:25,500
think I'm a pretty good catch?

979
01:03:26,270 --> 01:03:27,270
Be honest.

980
01:03:28,400 --> 01:03:29,470
Are you serious?

981
01:03:29,870 --> 01:03:31,540
If you don't shut me down
every now and then,

982
01:03:32,010 --> 01:03:33,010
do you get lockjaw?

983
01:03:37,080 --> 01:03:38,650
You may be a bit cold,

984
01:03:39,780 --> 01:03:41,280
but I know you're a good person.

985
01:03:42,120 --> 01:03:43,120
I can just tell.

986
01:03:45,750 --> 01:03:48,690
Okay. We'll end on that high note.

987
01:03:49,460 --> 01:03:50,460
Okay.

988
01:03:50,790 --> 01:03:52,760
Make sure you get relieved in the morning.

989
01:03:53,660 --> 01:03:54,660
I will.

990
01:04:22,890 --> 01:04:24,890
So coffee's not allowed either?

991
01:04:25,590 --> 01:04:26,930
Probably not.

992
01:04:27,700 --> 01:04:29,670
Go ask them, just to be sure.

993
01:04:34,540 --> 01:04:35,800
When did they say the test was?

994
01:04:35,870 --> 01:04:37,670
They said they'd let us know
30 minutes beforehand.

995
01:04:40,510 --> 01:04:41,510
The red phone?

996
01:04:42,780 --> 01:04:43,780
I brought it.

997
01:04:55,260 --> 01:04:57,290
If you'd gone to the ER,
you wouldn't have been seen right away.

998
01:04:57,930 --> 01:04:59,630
They would've run all kinds
of tests on you,

999
01:04:59,630 --> 01:05:00,760
and you'd be on medication
for over ten days.

1000
01:05:03,430 --> 01:05:04,570
(Kim Gwang Cheol,
Jin Ju's Biological Father)

1001
01:05:12,210 --> 01:05:14,410
- Hello?
- This is Jin Ju's father.

1002
01:05:15,510 --> 01:05:16,510
Hello.

1003
01:05:17,250 --> 01:05:18,850
I'd like to meet with you.

1004
01:05:19,780 --> 01:05:21,950
- I'm sorry?
- I said I want to meet.

1005
01:05:25,090 --> 01:05:26,090
Okay.

1006
01:05:32,390 --> 01:05:34,330
(Nua General Hospital)

1007
01:05:50,980 --> 01:05:52,080
(The Mind)

1008
01:06:02,320 --> 01:06:04,290
(Director Shin)

1009
01:06:08,200 --> 01:06:10,030
(Director Shin)

1010
01:06:12,470 --> 01:06:15,800
- What are you up to?
- Reading and listening to some music.

1011
01:06:16,510 --> 01:06:17,770
Because you're scared of the rain?

1012
01:06:19,440 --> 01:06:20,440
Are you outside?

1013
01:06:21,210 --> 01:06:22,210
Yes.

1014
01:06:23,080 --> 01:06:25,010
It's raining. You should get home.

1015
01:06:25,510 --> 01:06:26,650
I came because it's raining.

1016
01:06:28,050 --> 01:06:29,320
You're here?

1017
01:06:29,790 --> 01:06:30,850
Yes.

1018
01:06:31,450 --> 01:06:32,590
You're at my apartment complex?

1019
01:06:33,190 --> 01:06:34,190
Yes.

1020
01:06:34,820 --> 01:06:35,960
I feel weird about coming up.

1021
01:06:36,960 --> 01:06:38,160
Come down for a minute.

1022
01:06:40,600 --> 01:06:41,600
Or should I come up?

1023
01:06:42,130 --> 01:06:43,130
I came empty-handed, though.

1024
01:06:51,210 --> 01:06:53,010
(Jaeil Apartments)

1025
01:06:53,210 --> 01:06:54,740
Going down to the first floor.

1026
01:07:23,570 --> 01:07:26,580
What brings you here?
And you even drove yourself.

1027
01:07:27,540 --> 01:07:28,710
You haven't been drinking, have you?

1028
01:07:30,410 --> 01:07:31,550
Are you asking if I came here drunk?

1029
01:07:32,610 --> 01:07:33,620
No.

1030
01:07:35,380 --> 01:07:36,720
You get scared when it rains.

1031
01:07:38,250 --> 01:07:40,320
You remembered that?

1032
01:07:43,160 --> 01:07:44,490
A little rain like this is fine.

1033
01:07:46,060 --> 01:07:47,130
My gosh!

1034
01:08:50,390 --> 01:08:53,260
(Doctor Shin)

1035
01:08:53,530 --> 01:08:56,630
- Don't get too close to Ju Shin.
- Why?

1036
01:08:56,700 --> 01:08:57,700
You saw what happened with Momo.

1037
01:08:57,700 --> 01:08:58,970
But I've decided I want to get married.

1038
01:08:59,200 --> 01:09:01,800
- Please, don't even think about it.
- Do you have any ramyeon?

1039
01:09:01,870 --> 01:09:04,040
- Are you dating Ba Ra?
- We're not quite at that stage yet.

1040
01:09:04,170 --> 01:09:05,440
Don't lead her on.

1041
01:09:07,440 --> 01:09:09,340
- Are you okay?
- This is delicious.

1042
01:09:09,340 --> 01:09:11,780
Do you really think my Jin Ju is dead?

1043
01:09:11,780 --> 01:09:13,020
Did you meet with him?

1044
01:09:13,080 --> 01:09:16,220
- What have you all done?
- Search all you want.

1045
01:09:16,620 --> 01:09:19,560
Kim Gwang Cheol can run, but I can fly.

1046
01:09:19,620 --> 01:09:21,620
Didn't he just dump Momo for Ba Ra?

1047
01:09:21,920 --> 01:09:24,560
It's no contest. I like a total old man.

1048
01:09:24,630 --> 01:09:26,330
Why Geum Ba Ra of all people?

1049
01:09:27,100 --> 01:09:29,630
You want me to pull my hair back
to prove I'm Kim Jin Ju?

1050
01:09:29,700 --> 01:09:31,600
You want me to give you
Kim Jin Ju's face back?

1051
01:09:31,770 --> 01:09:36,410
If only you could make
my fantasy a reality.

1052
01:09:36,870 --> 01:09:39,140
Why'd you propose to Ba Ra
and make her leave?

1053
01:09:39,140 --> 01:09:41,940
- Leave?
- She said goodbye to me yesterday.

